what is the best time to trim a oak tree fall or winter is best i'm less worried about bleeding with oaks and more worried about the transmission of diseases oak wilt and other diseases have no cure and are moved from cut to cut but when the plant is dormant the disease doesn't travel try to have your tools sterilized before and after the pruning i hope that this helps good luck Pruning Sudden Oak Death Pruning fruit trees Oak Olive Fireblight Apple Gypsy moth Bacteria Upholstery Ebola Chestnut Allegheny National Forest Comfrey Sexually-transmitted infection Chlamydia Alpha-beta pruning Bamboo The Star Wars Holiday Special Wheat Phytophthora cinnamomi Tattoo Tobacco Cigarette Grafting Collision detection Bonsai Fruit tree propagation Fecal incontinence Bioterrorism Leprosy Acorn Apical dominance Sterilization (microbiology) Herpes simplex virus Economic history of Canada Yosemite National Park 2003 North America blackout Red Faction Elm Tekken characters Anemia Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Malaria Prostate cancer Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Luck Apricot Tuberculosis Compost Hepatitis C Incarnations of Immortality Theory of constraints Leukemia Crohn's disease Legionellosis Transmissible spongiform encephalopathy Pedunculate oak Weapons of Middle-earth Lawn mower Fisting Vitamin C Shrub Coppicing Knife Ascension Oat Pre-Confederation history of Canada Appomattox Campaign Latitude Deforestation Pelvic inflammatory disease Computer chess The Amber Spyglass Stomach cancer Smallpox Europe Gardening Pok__mon Live! Infectious disease Food Yellow fever Cork Oak Tsetse fly Branch and bound James Augustus Grant Tomato Acute myelogenous leukemia Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Chagas disease Boat building Surveillance Flowering plant Piccolo Junior Saga Genetically modified food Phoebe Halliwell Bougainvillea RuneScape skills Shamanism 